text: The Najarians are not shady King Jack.

As far as I know Pete and Jon are great guys - hard working and charitable. But without quantifying the success/failure of their ideas one can not evaluate the strategy and service. Stated simply. As I have suggested, @CNBC should get an intern to compile the data. Easy peasey.

You got the right idea. I don't think alot of people get it. I think the Najarians are great guys. They are charitable and hard workers. But directional call buying is the hardest game there is and without chronicling the results - the value of the strategy and service suspect.
